			<ns0:name>jvo...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/102292187274959663599/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">For: http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2821, we currently include SCons tests (those that generate pexes and which run under the IRT).

However, we rely on rev AAAA of the pexes, and rev BBBB of the SConstruct/nacl checkout. This means that:

# This will have to be updated whenever there are changes to the tests, e.g.
# new tests, different expected outcomes, etc.
# ...
ARCHIVED_PEXE_SCONS_REV=AAAA

(see buildbot/buildbot_pnacl_toolchain_tests.sh)


We don't really want to have to update the rev of the pexes whenever there is a change to the set of tests.  We would lose the ability to test pexes generated by old frontends (since the newer rev of pexes were generated by a newer frontend).


Instead, the test script could check out an old frontend and generate the pexes while accounting for changes and additions to tests.  That would give us bitcode generated by an old frontend, and we could still handle new tests.

There may be cases where a test breaks under the old frontend, so we may need a mechanism to mark &amp;quot;is_broken&amp;quot; for such cases.
